<div id="review_2046199354" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2046199354" />
    <a title="Paula" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3066032-paula"><img alt="Paula" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1335291149p2/3066032.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2046199354?book_show_action=true">Aug 15, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Paula" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Paula" href="/user/show/3066032-paula">Paula</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2046199354" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8863490545837645884">Dreadfully boring. From the synopsis, I thought it would be about old letters &amp; family history. It was actually about a modern-day woman who is learning to live without her dead husband. Took forever to finally start reading the letters (so long I almost ditched the book). Well-written &amp; deep, but NOT what I was expecting &amp; NOT what I was in the mood to read. I also really disliked &quot;Kate imagines...&quot; rather than telling me what actually happened in the past.</span>
  <span id="freeText8863490545837645884" style="display:none">Dreadfully boring. From the synopsis, I thought it would be about old letters &amp; family history. It was actually about a modern-day woman who is learning to live without her dead husband. Took forever to finally start reading the letters (so long I almost ditched the book). Well-written &amp; deep, but NOT what I was expecting &amp; NOT what I was in the mood to read. I also really disliked "Kate imagines..." rather than telling me what actually happened in the past.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8863490545837645884" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

