    <a title="Anna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7256419-anna"><img alt="Anna" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2443694716?book_show_action=true">Jul 03, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anna" href="/user/show/7256419-anna">Anna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780676976403" href="/book/show/6348276-the-hatbox-letters">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2443694716" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18088932457213767367">This is a beautiful book, rich with the textures of the past. Powning has a gift for description that teases out what really matters in our lives. It is a slow book, I guess, but I think it has to be, because it is about dealing with loss and learning to value memory.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

